# Writerdeck for reMarkable 1

Migration 2 Phase A (pure math/undo ‚Üí `EditHelper`) shipped @ fork `a92ad2b`. Phase B/C handoff: [docs/editor-migration-2-to-cpp/todo-handoff-edit-helper-cpp.md](docs/editor-migration-2-to-cpp/todo-handoff-edit-helper-cpp.md).

## Audience and replies

The owner is a **designer with basic code skills**, not a professional developer. Unless they ask for depth: keep chat replies **terse**, in **plain layman‚Äôs prose**, and lead with what happened / what to do next. Avoid jargon dumps, long architecture digressions, and ‚Äúwhat we didn‚Äôt do‚Äù lists. Save technical detail for commits, handoff docs, and when asked.

## Drivers

Document integrity is the absolute paramount driver ‚Äî the owner's prose must survive as plain Markdown on disk. That outranks feature speed and harness cosmetics. See [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) ¬ß Document integrity, [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md), [docs/integrity-audit.md](docs/integrity-audit.md). Before inventing editor behavior, check how similar editors do it (CodeMirror, Qt `TextEdit`, Mac/Linux text fields) and prefer proven patterns.

## Verify before calling work done (mandatory ‚Äî do not skip)

**Deploy success ‚âÝ tested. curl/API 200 ‚âÝ UI works.**

After `daemon/`, `build-keywriter.sh`, Lobby/QML (fork), or deploy-script changes:

### Phone browser UI (required for any `daemon/*.js` / embedded HTML/CSS change)

`curl` cannot catch ES module load failures ‚Äî the page can show static `connecting...` with zero JS running.

1. Deploy (`deploy-rmkbd.sh`; ensure `systemctl start writerdeck` if service stopped)
2. **Load the page** at `http://$RM_HOST:8000/` (browser tools or real browser) ‚Äî hard refresh if cached
3. Confirm **JavaScript actually ran**:
   - Notes list populated (not empty with only the static top bar)
   - Connection bar shows **Connected** or **Tablet offline** ‚Äî not stuck on HTML default `connecting...`
   - PIN screen hidden when `pinDigits` is `none`
4. Spot-check changed UI (e.g. Sync setup modal, Save/Sync buttons)
5. If modules fail to load, fix before moving on (common: duplicate `export` in `connection.js`)

### Tablet / server (required for all deploys)

1. Rebuild Writerdeck if QML/C++ changed ‚Üí push fork if needed ‚Üí `git push` (this repo) ‚Üí `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` ‚Üí `deploy-keywriter.sh -b`
2. SSH ‚Üí `journalctl -u writerdeck -n 30` ‚Äî fail on QML parse errors or instant `editor process exited`
3. `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh` after Writerdeck/QML deploy
4. `bash scripts/test-keyboard-harness.sh --fast` after QML arrow, selection, or `handleKey` changes (see `docs/decisions.md` #13). Sign-off: full suite **110/110/0**. Critical gate: `-t critical --fast` ‚Üí **38/38/0**. Update [milestone-runs.md](docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md) after every full suite. While iterating keyboard bugs, triage all failures before deploying ‚Äî at most one Writerdeck binary deploy per session unless QML fails to launch (see `docs/editor-testing/todo.md`, `docs/lessons.md` ¬ß Harness batch workflow).
5. `bash scripts/test-lobby-keyboard.sh` after Lobby, `handleHome`, or `lobbyFocus` changes (see `docs/decisions.md` #15)

Run all applicable steps every time without being asked. Do not declare done with known gaps ("not yet on tablet", "should work"). Do not run edit-session and keyboard harness in parallel.

## Time budget while debugging

No built-in task timer. Estimate elapsed time from message timestamps and shell command durations (deploy logs, harness runs).

After about 20 minutes on one task without reaching sign-off, stop implementing. Report to the user: what you tried, what consumed time, whether you followed cheapest-proof-first and iterate-vs-sign-off ([lessons.md](docs/lessons.md) ¬ß Device verify and iteration), and what you would do next. Ask before another full deploy+E2E cycle. Keyboard harness iteration: one triage run, batch fixes, one Writerdeck deploy ‚Äî not push/deploy per scenario.

Do not `pkill -f /home/root/Writerdeck` (matches Writerdeck-server). On-device naming: `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/decisions.md` #29.

## Constraints

- No jailbreak; preserve OTA ‚Üí avoid Toltec
- Static Go only: `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm GOARM=7`
- Markdown save format
- Cross-compile Writerdeck-server on Mac; never local `docker build` for Writerdeck ‚Äî CI/GHA + `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh`
- Do not grow new editor behavior in `build-keywriter.sh` ‚Äî edit the fork ([docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) ¬ß4)

## Dev setup

Secrets: `secrets/remarkable.local.env`; scripts source `scripts/_env.sh` for `RM_HOST`.

**Daemon:** `deploy-rmkbd.sh` ‚Üí `systemctl restart writerdeck`. Verify APIs **and** load the phone UI (see above) ‚Äî not `curl` alone.

**Writerdeck:** editor changes in Writerdeck-keywriter ‚Üí push fork ‚Üí this repo CI (or wait for rebuild) ‚Üí `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` ‚Üí `deploy-keywriter.sh -b`. Relaunch Writerdeck after binary deploy (server restart alone is not enough). Then `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh`; `bash scripts/test-lobby-keyboard.sh` after Lobby/`handleHome` QML; `bash scripts/test-keyboard-harness.sh` when keyboard/selection QML changed.

GitHub token: browser `localStorage ghToken` + tablet RAM via `POST /api/sync/token`; after restart WebSocket `needtoken` triggers auto-repost. Logs: `journalctl -u writerdeck.service` ‚Äî token restore shows `sync reconcile (token)` after `client connected` (see `docs/server-sync-implementation.md`).

## Documentation

Write like John Gruber: complete sentences, direct, minimal formatting ‚Äî almost no bold, no emoji, no `Status: built` scaffolding. Prose over bullet dumps; use tables only when the data is inherently tabular (e.g. browser vs tablet), not as default structure. Short cross-links at the top, not boilerplate on every file.

Terse and forward-looking. Keep durable operational commands and lessons (what worked, what didn't, why). Prune settled history, chatty narration, and decisions that won't help anyone extending the project later. When in doubt, keep ‚Äî but don't pad.

Standing docs only: `TODO.md`, `DONE.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/decisions.md`, `docs/lessons.md`. How ‚Üí architecture; why ‚Üí decisions; gotchas ‚Üí lessons. No new summary markdown files. Prune dead scripts/files when paths close; grep references first.

## Encoding

Executable/device files (`.sh`, `.service`, `.go`, `.yml`, Dockerfile): ASCII-only + LF, no BOM. Markdown `.md`: Unicode OK. Before committing scripts: grep for `[^\x00-\x7F]` ‚Äî must be empty for `.sh`/`.ps1`.
